OL,3,CWife sentenced for murdering husband
OL,4,Cand hiding his body in their garden
OL,6,FMaureen Rickards, 50, stabbed Jeremy
OL,7,FRickards, 65, to death, then spent
OL,8,Fmoney on his bank card, concocted lies
OL,9,Fto try to divert suspicion away from
OL,10,Fherself, and got rid of evidence and
OL,11,Fthe murder weapon, Canterbury Crown
OL,12,FCourt heard.
OL,14,FShe had been abusive, violent and
OL,15,Fcontrolling in the build-up to the
OL,16,Fkilling, the court was told, and his
OL,17,Fremains were discovered at their
OL,18,FCanterbury address by police on July
OL,19,F11 last year, six days after he was
OL,20,Freported missing by his stepdaughter.
